    <a class="time-icons time-icons-tw social-link-tw popup" href="#" data-href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwp.me%2Fp5HMd-eWj4&text=A%20Shadow%20Falls%20on%20China&via=TIMEWorld" data-event="tweet" title="Click to Tweet this article"></a>
    <a class="time-icons time-icons-linkedin social-link-linkedin popup" href="http://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&url=http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3560726%2Fa-shadow-falls-on-china%2F&title=A+Shadow+Falls+on+China" data-event="linkedin" title="Click to post this article to LinkedIn"></a>
    <a href="#" class="time-icons time-icons-comment toggle-comments" data-lf-site-id="314099" data-lf-article-id="3560726" data-url="http://time.com/3560726/a-shadow-falls-on-china/" data-title="A Shadow Falls on China" title="Click to view and post comments" data-event="comment-click">0</a>
        <div class="reprintLink"><a href="https://s100.copyright.com/AppDispatchServlet?publisherName=TIME&amp;publication=TIME&amp;title=A%20Shadow%20Falls%20on%20China&amp;publicationDate=11/06/2014&amp;author=Rana%20Foroohar&amp;contentID=3560726&amp;orderBeanReset=true" data-event="reprints" title="Click to order a reprint of this article">Order a Reprint</a>
        </div>
</span>
</aside><p>Will the next global financial crisis be manufactured in China? That&rsquo;s a question raised by the most recent report on the shadow-banking sector, from the Financial Stability Board (FSB), a group in Switzerland that coordinates the work of the world&rsquo;s financial regulators. Shadow banks are that mysterious collection of hedge funds, money-market funds and private lenders that operate outside the regulatory scrutiny of the formal banking sector. &#8230;</p>
  </section>
