</article><article class="clearfix full-article has-hero-image  time_article " id="article-3490118" data-article="3490118" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article">
  <header class="article-header">
    
    <section class="tags ">
  		  <a class="brand-tag brand-time-tag" href="http://time.com/" data-bypass="true">TIME</a>



            <a class="topic-tag" itemprop="articleSection" href="http://time.com/tag/walmart/" data-event="tag-walmart" data-bypass="true">Walmart</a>

      </section>
    <h2 class="article-title" itemprop="headline">Why Walmart Workers Losing Healthcare Might Not Be Bad</h2>
  <div class="article-sub-headline">
    <div class="article-meta">

        <ul class="article-authors">
            <li class="article-author ">
              <span class="byline"><a itemprop="author" href="https://time.com/author/rana-foroohar/">Rana Foroohar</a></span>
              <a class="author-twitter" target="_blank" href="https://twitter.com/RanaForoohar">@RanaForoohar</a>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <time class="publish-date" itemprop="datePublished" datetime="2014-10-10 10:58:10" pubdate>Oct. 10, 2014</time>
      
    </div>
    <div class="social-links">
      <a class="expand-share" href="javascript:void 0;" data-event="exp-micro" title="Click to view article share options">SHARE</a>
    <span class="social-links-tooltip">
    	<a class="time-icons time-icons-mail social-link-mail" href="mailto:?subject=Why%20Walmart%20Workers%20Losing%20Healthcare%20Might%20Not%20Be%20Bad%20%7C%20TIME&body=Why%20Walmart%20Workers%20Losing%20Healthcare%20Might%20Not%20Be%20Bad%0A%0AIronies%20abound%0A%0Ahttp%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3490118%2Fwalmart-healthcare%2F" data-event="email" title="Click to Email this article"></a>
    	<a class="time-icons time-icons-fb social-link-fb popup" href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3490118%2Fwalmart-healthcare%2F" data-event="fb-share" title="Click to post this article to Facebook"></a>
    	<a class="time-icons time-icons-tw social-link-tw popup" href="#" data-href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=http%3A%2F%2Fti.me%2F1qDuKAQ&text=Why%20Walmart%20Workers%20Losing%20Healthcare%20Might%20Not%20Be%20Bad&via=TIME" data-event="tweet" title="Click to Tweet this article"></a>
    	<a class="time-icons time-icons-gplus social-link-gplus popup" href="https://plus.google.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3490118%2Fwalmart-healthcare%2F" data-event="google+" title="Click to post this article to Google+"></a>
    	<a class="time-icons time-icons-linkedin social-link-linkedin popup" href="http://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&url=http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3490118%2Fwalmart-healthcare%2F&title=Why+Walmart+Workers+Losing+Healthcare+Might+Not+Be+Bad" data-event="linkedin" title="Click to post this article to LinkedIn"></a>
    	
    </span>    </div>
  </div>  </header>  <section class="article-body" itemprop="articleBody">
    
    <figure class="landscape">
      <img src="http://timedotcom.files.wordpress.com/2014/08/walmart.jpg?w=280" itemprop="image" alt="" srcset="http://timedotcom.files.wordpress.com/2014/08/walmart.jpg?w=1100 800w, http://timedotcom.files.wordpress.com/2014/08/walmart.jpg?w=1100 800w 2x"/>
      <figcaption class="image-caption">
        
        <span class="credit">Getty Images</span>
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
	<h2 class="article-excerpt" itemprop="alternativeHeadline">Ironies abound</h2>
    <p>Talk about irony. In the same week that Walmart announced employees who work less than 30 hours will be losing their health care coverage, the company also announced that it&#8217;d be getting deeper into the business of selling insurance, making it easier for customers to price shop for insurance in stores. In some ways, this mirrors Walmart&#8217;s overall business model&mdash;keep prices down for consumers, but keep wages and benefits for employees low too.</p>
<p>Ironically, under the rules of Obamacare, it&rsquo;s possible that those part time employees will get a better deal on health care exchanges, thanks to subsidies that help lower income <a href="http://www.vox.com/2014/10/7/6939057/walmart-drops-insurance-good-news" target="_blank">workers buy insurance</a>. It&rsquo;s all part of the new landscape created by the Affordable Care Act. As Obamacare turns one year old, Joe Nocera and I discussed how it&rsquo;s changed healthcare, business, and the economy, on WNYC&rsquo;s Money Talking.</p>
			<form id="wpcom-iframe-form-d73215303d5bcc58dff130436cdcb10f-5470373881181" target="wpcom-iframe-d73215303d5bcc58dff130436cdcb10f-5470373881181" method="post" action="//wpcomwidgets.com/?wpcom_origin=http%3A%2F%2Ftimedotcom.wordpress.com" style="display: none">
